Question: How to get the IP address of the server which is running on the same network as the client: I have a server which is running on the same network as the client. I want to get the IP address of the server. I have tried this:
InetAddress addr = InetAddress.getLocalHost();
String ip = addr.getHostAddress();

But it gives me the IP address of the client.
Please using this api: InetAddress.getLocalHost.
Answer:<<<api>>>: InetAddress.getLocalHost
<<<code>>>: InetAddress addr = InetAddress.getByName("server.domain.com");
String ip = addr.getHostAddress();
<<<explanation>>>: You need to get the IP address of the server by name.
